HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 112
BY REPRESENTATIVE JACKSON
A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
To urge and request that the Louisiana Department of Transportation and Development
(DOTD), in conjunction with DOTD District 4, study the recent occurrences of
rainwater flooding along the Louisiana Highway 1 corridor in Shreveport, Louisiana,
extending from its intersection with East Stoner Avenue to its intersection with East
Kings Highway and Louisiana Highway 3032.
WHEREAS, Louisiana Highway 1 is a major north-south business and residential
thoroughfare in Shreveport; and
WHEREAS, this segment of Louisiana Highway 1 has experienced recent recurring
and significant flooding during rain events; and
WHEREAS, the recurring flooding along this segment of Louisiana Highway 1 has
impeded access to residences and businesses, disrupted vehicular traffic, and posed threats
to public safety; and
WHEREAS, a coordinated study with the participation of affected neighborhoods
and businesses and relevant local municipal entities is necessary to identify the causes of and
solutions to the flooding along this corridor.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
urge and request that the Louisiana DOTD, in conjunction with DOTD District 4, study the
recent occurrences of rainwater flooding along the Louisiana Highway 1 corridor in
Shreveport, Louisiana, extending from its intersection with East Stoner Avenue to its
intersection with East Kings Highway and Louisiana Highway 3032.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the DOTD shall organize and conduct no less
than two public forums with affected residents and business owners to gather feedback and
insight regarding the impacts of the recent recurring flooding along the corridor.
