BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the DOTD shall incorporate the input, expertise,
and support of relevant local municipal entities, including but not limited to the Shreveport
Public Works Department, the Shreveport Department of Operational Services, Office of
Water and Sewerage, Shreveport Traffic Engineering, and Caddo Parish Office of Homeland
Security.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the DOTD shall submit a written report detailing
its findings and recommendations, including proposed plans to mitigate the flooding during
rain events, for inclusion in DOTD's Statewide Flood Control Program, to the joint
transportation, highways, and public works committee at least sixty days prior to the
convening of the 2027 Regular Session.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the DOTD shall submit a copy of the report to
the state representative for Louisiana House District No. 2 and the state senator for Louisiana
Senate District No. 39 at least sixty days prior to the convening of the 2027 Regular Session.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of the Resolution be transmitted to the
secretary of the DOTD.
